ce:section.ce:para:
In order to verify whether the g-C3N4/NS-CQDs composite has peroxidase-like activity, the catalytic activity of the composite was investigated with TMB as substrate. We also constructed the g-C3N4/NS-CQDs-TMB-H2O2 system for verification. Colorless TMB will be oxidized in the catalytic process to form the blue oxidation product ox TMB (Fig. 9
                           ), while ox TMB has the maximum absorbance at λ = 652 nm. According to Fig. 10
                            a, in the absence of g-C3N4/NS-CQDs, the TMB+H2O2 system has almost no absorbance at 652 nm. In the absence of H2O2, g-C3N4/NS-CQDs and TMB produced a weak absorption peak, indicating that g-C3N4/NS-CQDs may have weak oxidase activity. However, the catalytic ability is too small to be discussed. Only when g-C3N4/NS-CQDs-TMB-H2O2 exists at the same time, the absorbance increases obviously, which can prove that g-C3N4 /NS-CQDs have peroxidase-like activity. Compare the peroxidase-like activity by changing the catalytic materials in the system; the catalytic activity of block g-C3N4 is deficient, and the catalytic activity of g-C3N4 nanosheets is improved. At the same time, compared with NS-CQDs, NS-CQDS shows relatively high catalytic activity but is still not high. However, the g-C3N4 nanoplate /NS-CQDs nanoenzyme showed greatly enhanced catalytic activity, which was nearly three times higher than that of the g-C3N4 nanoplate, and the reaction solution was dark blue (Fig. 10 b, inset). The above results may be because g-C3N4 nanosheets have a larger specific surface area and can be doped better than bulk g-C3N4 nanosheets. It is beneficial to the uniform distribution of NS-CQDs on its surface, improving stability and reducing the agglomeration of quantum dots.

Based on the above reaction mechanism, a colorimetric glucose detection system based on 7NSC-g nano-enzyme was constructed under the best experimental conditions. As shown in Fig. 17
                            a, the ultraviolet absorption spectra of different glucose concentrations, We can see from Fig. 17 b that the absorbance at λ = 652 nm increases with the increase of glucose concentration. There is an excellent linear relationship in the range of 10–400 μM: A=0.00014C glucose + 0.0818(R2 = 0.9915), and the detection limit is 1.63 μM, which is lower than the LOD of most similar nanoenzyme materials for glucose detection (Table 4
                           ).
